# StudyFlow – VS Code Steps Checklist
> All steps you need to complete in VS Code for the Backend Development Walkthrough (Part 2)

---

## Step 10 — Install the Supabase Client & Set Up Config Files

### 1. Install the Supabase JS library
Open a terminal in VS Code and run:
```bash
npm install @supabase/supabase-js
```

### 2. Create src/lib/supabase.js
```js
import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js'

const supabaseUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_SUPABASE_URL
const supabaseAnonKey = import.meta.env.VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

export const supabase = createClient(supabaseUrl, supabaseAnonKey)
```

### 3. Create .env in the project root
```env
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://guouslhlbliprrigkytt.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_key_here
```
> Replace your_anon_key_here with the real anon key from:
> Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API Keys > Legacy tab > anon public

### 4. Add .env to .gitignore
Open (or create) .gitignore in the project root and make sure it contains:
```
.env
```

